quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  27,1,"Tâ Sîn. Those are the signs{1}of the Recital{2}and an Evident Scripture—",footnotes:1:[The Arabic word used is <i>ayat</i> (singular <i>ayah</i>). <i>Ayah</i> means ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Qur’an, like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose. Each such unit is considered a ‘sign’ from God.],footnotes:2:[The Arabic word used is Quran which means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.]
  27,2,"guidance and glad tidings for the believers"
  27,3,"who establish the prayer and bring{1}the purifying charity{2}and, of the Hereafter, they are certain.",footnotes:1:[The Qur’an always uses verb ‘to bring’ rather than verb ‘to give’ in association with charity; this should be pondered by the reader.],footnotes:2:[The Arabic word used is z<i>akāt</i>, which denotes purification and growth.]
  27,4,"Indeed, those who do not believe in the Hereafter—We have adorned their deeds for them, so they wander aimlessly;"
  27,5,"those are the ones for whom is the worst punishment, and in the Hereafter they are the biggest losers."
  27,6,"And indeed, you<sup>sg </sup>are surely receiving the Recital<sup>b </sup>from One who is All-Wise, All-Knowing.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Quran which means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  27,7,"Recall when Moses said to his family, “I have surely glimpsed a fire. I will bring you some news from it, or bring you a firebrand, a borrowed flame{1}, that you may warm yourselves.”",footnotes:1:Qira’at: Nafie’, Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr, Ibn Amer and Abu Ja’far read it as: “…or bring you a firebrand of a borrowed flame,”
  27,8,"Then when he reached it, he was called: “Blessed is whoever is in the fire and whoever is around it, and Highly Exalted is Allah, Lord of all realms."
  27,9,"O Moses, it is indeed I, Allah, the Almighty, the All-Wise."
  27,10,"Now, cast your staff.” So when he saw it shaking as though it were a snake, he turned away, fleeing, and did not look back. “O Moses, fear not! Truly, in My presence emissaries have nothing to fear,"
